# Category Tree

Use this file as the starter tree block before indexing the full notebook. Copy it into the top of `index.md`, above the `---` separator.

Rules of thumb:
- Keep exactly three hierarchy layers before note leaves.
- Aim for roughly 5-10 children at each level.
- Prefer durable category names over narrow project-specific labels.
- Add a new subtree only when several concepts clearly do not fit the current tree.

